# Code Rules (TS / React / State / API / Tests)

## TypeScript

- `strict: true`, `noUncheckedIndexedAccess`, `exactOptionalPropertyTypes`, `useUnknownInCatchVariables`.
- Infer domain types from Zod: `type X = z.infer<typeof XSchema>`.
- Branded types for IDs. Discriminated unions over boolean flags. `readonly` for immutable data.
- Use `import type { ... }`. Catch as `unknown`, narrow with `instanceof`.
- Never: `any`, non-null `!` on possibly-undefined, `as` on network data (use `Schema.parse()`), enums (use `as const` objects).

## Components

- Functional only. One component per file, `PascalCase.tsx`.
- Destructure props at top; default values in destructuring. Explicit prop types (no `React.FC` unless using implicit `children`).
- Keep <150 LOC; split when it grows. No business logic in UI (no fetching, no Zod parsing, no heavy aggregation).
- Semantic HTML first. Icon-only buttons need `aria-label`. Visible focus rings. Keyboard-operable.
- Event handlers: prop `onX`, internal `handleX`.

## Hooks

- Prefix `use`. Feature-only → `features/<f>/hooks/`; generic → `shared/hooks/`.
- Move fetching, URL state, form state, pagination, subscriptions into hooks.
- `useEffect` is last resort — derive during render. Every effect with a subscription/timer MUST cleanup.
- Never sync derived state back into state with `useEffect`.

## State — pick the right tool

| Kind                              | Tool                              |
| --------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Local UI                          | `useState` / `useReducer`         |
| Derived                           | Compute in render / `useMemo`     |
| URL-shareable (filters, paging)   | `useSearchParams` / `useUrlState` |
| Shared in subtree                 | React Context (guard hook)        |
| Frequently-updating global UI     | Zustand (typed selectors)         |
| Server data                       | **React Query — no exceptions**   |
| Forms                             | React Hook Form + Zod             |
| Preferences                       | `useLocalStorage`                 |

- Never duplicate server data into Context or Zustand.
- Context: one per concern, expose a guard hook (`useAuth` throws if missing Provider), never expose raw context.
- Zustand: never store server data; always consume via selectors.

## API layer

- All HTTP goes through `shared/api/apiClient.ts` (wraps `fetch`).
- `apiRequest` **requires** a Zod `schema` — response is validated before return.
- Typed errors: `HttpError`, `NetworkError`, `ValidationError` (from `shared/api/ApiError.ts`).
- Services in `features/<f>/services/`. React-free. Map DTO → domain when shapes differ. Accept optional `AbortSignal`.
- Hooks wrap `useQuery` / `useMutation`. Query keys as a `const` tree: `keys.all`, `keys.list(p)`, `keys.detail(id)`. Never string-concat keys.
- Pass `signal` from `queryFn({ signal })` into the service.
- Mutations invalidate the narrowest scope. Auth via HttpOnly cookies (`credentials: 'include'`); tokens in memory only if unavoidable.

## Routing

- Pages are lazy-loaded: `lazy(() => import('@/features/.../pages/XPage').then(m => ({ default: m.XPage })))`.
- Path strings only in `routes/paths.ts`. Navigate via `<Link to={paths.x}>` / `useNavigate()`.
- Routes reference pages only; layouts own chrome (`<Outlet />`).

## Naming

| Element                  | Convention                     |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------ |
| Component / type / schema| `PascalCase`, schemas suffix `Schema` |
| Hook                     | `useCamelCase`                 |
| Service                  | `<noun>Service`                |
| Constant                 | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`             |
| Boolean                  | `is/has/can/should` prefix     |
| Handler prop / internal  | `onX` / `handleX`              |
| Env var                  | `VITE_UPPER_SNAKE`             |
| CSS Module class         | `camelCase`                    |
| CSS variable             | `--kebab-case`                 |
| Test file                | `*.test.ts(x)`                 |
| Folder                   | `kebab-case` or single word    |

Acronyms in type/function names: `PascalCase` (`HttpClient`, not `HTTPClient`).

## Testing

- Vitest + RTL + MSW + `user-event`. Render via `renderWithProviders` (`src/test/test-utils.tsx`) with a **fresh QueryClient per test**.
- Query priority: `getByRole` + `name` → `getByLabelText` → `getByText` → `getByTestId` (last resort).
- Use `userEvent`, not `fireEvent`. Use `findBy*` for async; no arbitrary `waitFor` timeouts.
- Mock network with MSW, never `vi.spyOn(global, 'fetch')`.
- Coverage gate: `lib/` and `services/` ≥ 80% lines & functions. No full-tree snapshots.

## Security

- Validate all inbound payloads with Zod.
- Avoid `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`; if unavoidable, sanitize with DOMPurify.
- Never log PII or card numbers in the client.
